The paper deals with the multiterminal cut problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of graph algorithms. The paper introduces new data reduction rules and uses a branch-and-reduce framework, which are techniques commonly used in the design of algorithms for combinatorial optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the performance of the algorithm, which suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents an exact algorithm, which is a subfield of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
